content:
Given a JSON data with news articles, can you analyze and classify each article based on its content and provide the category it belongs to, whether it's "Unforeseen Occurrences," "Meteorological News," or "Regional Incidents"? Please include a reasoning behind your classification. 
JSON data example: 
{
  "news_articles": [
    {
      "title": "Tornado hits small town in Texas",
      "content": "A massive tornado touched down in the small town of Smithville, causing destruction and leaving many homeless. Local authorities are urging people to evacuate the area as more severe weather is expected in the coming days.",
      "location": "Smithville, Texas"
    },
    {
      "title": "Power outage affects entire city",
      "content": "A power outage caused by a damaged transformer left the entire city without electricity for several hours. Emergency services are working to restore power as soon as possible.",
      "location": "Citywide"
    },
    {
      "title": "Robbery at local bank",
      "content": "Two armed men robbed a local bank this morning, taking an undisclosed amount of money. Police are currently investigating the incident and urging anyone with information to come forward.",
      "location": "Downtown"
    }
  ]
}
